    "name": "Unfranchise Marketing OAuth",
    "description": "# Unfranchise Marketing OAuth Collection\n\nThis collection contains OAuth token and an example API Manager endpoint of the search-redirect server for 3 environments: **Dev**, **Staging**, and **Production**.\n\n---\n\n## OAuth Flow Overview\n\nThe full token lifecycle for building an application:\n\n1. **Authenticate** — `POST /oauth2/token` with `grant_type=password`, `client_id`, `username`, and `password` to obtain an `access_token` and `refresh_token`.\n2. **Use the token** — Pass the token in the `Authorization` header as `bearer <access_token>` on protected API endpoints.\n3. **Check token status** — `GET /oauth2/tokeninfo?access_token=<token>` to inspect expiration and user info.\n4. **Refresh the token** — `POST /oauth2/token` with `grant_type=refresh_token`, `refresh_token`, and `client_id` to get a new `access_token` without re-authenticating.\n\n---\n\n## Environment Base URLs\n\n| Environment | Base URL |\n|---|---|\n| Dev | `https://devoauthapi.mashop.com` |\n| Staging | `https://stagingoauthapi.mashop.com` |\n| Production | `https://oauthapi-gso.mashop.com` |\n\n---\n\n## Request & Response Reference\n\n### POST /oauth2/token (Password Grant)\n\n**Request body** (x-www-form-urlencoded):\n- `grant_type` = `password`\n- `client_id` = your application's client ID\n- `username` = the user's ID\n- `password` = the user's password\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n    \"access_token\": \"b314fd3b9de617db5773d8b626bd32e2\",\n    \"token_type\": \"bearer\",\n    \"expires_in\": 2592000,\n    \"refresh_token\": \"afda3dd22644bccdf9dd82a51926323c\"\n}\n```\n\n### POST /oauth2/token (Refresh Grant)\n\n**Request body** (x-www-form-urlencoded):\n- `grant_type` = `refresh_token`\n- `refresh_token` = the refresh token from the original authentication\n- `client_id` = your application's client ID\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n    \"access_token\": \"2b2d45b66b69ec1589791546058a8b2\",\n    \"token_type\": \"bearer\",\n    \"expires_in\": 2592000\n}\n```\n\n**Note:** The refresh response does **not** return a new `refresh_token`. Your application must hold onto the original `refresh_token` from the password grant and reuse it for future refreshes.\n\n### GET /oauth2/tokeninfo\n\n**Query parameter:** `access_token=<token>`\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n    \"accessToken\": \"396e6a91e17e818310f4e158272ccf0\",\n    \"tokenType\": \"bearer\",\n    \"issuedAt\": 1775683148,\n    \"expiresIn\": 2591992,\n    \"approvedScopes\": [],\n    \"userInfo\": {\n        \"uniqueId\": \"0001010\",\n        \"userName\": \"0001010\",\n        \"firstName\": \"\",\n        \"lastName\": \"\",\n        \"accountEnabled\": true,\n        \"organizationName\": \"default\",\n        \"attribtues\": {}\n    },\n    \"audience\": \"f7ed7c9495b84272913f9953a570544a\",\n    \"properties\": {\n        \"ufoid\": \"555555555\"\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Using the Token on Protected Endpoints\n\nPass the `access_token` in the `Authorization` header:\n```\nAuthorization: bearer <access_token>\n```\n\nSee the `search-redirect-oauth` request in each folder for an example.\n\n---\n\n## Token Expiration & Refresh Strategy\n\n- Access tokens expire after **30 days** (2,592,000 seconds).\n- Refreshed tokens also last **30 days**.\n- Use the **Token Info** endpoint to check remaining time via the `expiresIn` field.\n- Your application should store the `refresh_token` from the initial authentication and use it to refresh before the `access_token` expires.\n\n---\n\n## How to Use This Postman Collection\n\n1. **Import** this collection into Postman.\n2. **Open** the folder for the environment you want to test (Dev, Staging, or Production).\n3. **Run the \"oAuth Token\" request first.** This authenticates and automatically saves the `access_token` and `refresh_token` as collection variables.\n4. **Run the \"search-redirect-oauth\" request.** It automatically uses the token from step 3 in the Authorization header.\n5. **Run \"Token Info\"** to inspect the current token's expiration and user details.\n6. **Run \"Refresh Token\"** to get a new access token without re-authenticating.\n\n### Using the Collection Runner\n\nYou can also run an entire folder at once using Postman's **Collection Runner**:\n\n- Right-click the folder (e.g., Dev) and select **Run folder**.\n- The requests execute in order and tokens are passed automatically between requests.\n\n---\n\n## Important Notes\n\n- The username, password, and client_id are hardcoded test user values for consistency in Postman, but your application will need to dynamically pass in the username and password.\n- The `access_token` and `refresh_token` are stored as **collection variables** and are automatically set each time you run the token request.\n- No Postman environment variables are needed — everything is self-contained in this collection.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
